novel-timeline — End User License Agreement (EULA)
Last updated: 2026-04-21

This End User License Agreement ("EULA") governs the use of the software
novel-timeline ("Software") provided by the individual developer
Seo Il-seon ("Developer"). By installing or running the Software, you
("User") agree to be bound by all terms of this EULA.

NOTICE: This is an English translation provided for informational purposes.
In case of any inconsistency or conflict between this English translation
and the Korean original (see the `LICENSE` file), **the Korean version
shall prevail**.

1. License Grant
   The Developer grants the User a non-exclusive, non-transferable license
   to install and run the Software for personal or business use, subject
   to compliance with this EULA.

2. License Tiers
   - Free Trial: Free use of **all features** for ninety (90) days from
     the date of initial installation. No usage limits are applied during
     the trial. Trial eligibility is evaluated locally from the User's
     configuration file (`installDate`); no server registration or account
     sign-up is required.
   - Monthly Subscription: Monthly billing via Lemon Squeezy; full
     functionality during the paid period.
   - Annual Subscription: Annual billing via Lemon Squeezy; full
     functionality during the paid period.
   - (No perpetual license is offered.)

3. Behavior after trial or subscription expiry (Read-only mode)
   If the 90-day trial expires without an active paid subscription, OR an
   active subscription expires or is cancelled, the Software enters
   **Read-only mode**.
   - Permitted: Viewing existing projects; exporting in JSON/NTZ/TXT and
     other supported formats; entering a license key; changing theme,
     language, and other settings.
   - Blocked: Adding, modifying, or deleting events, characters,
     foreshadowings, relationships, collections, or factions; importing
     external files; creating new projects.
   - User data files are never altered or destroyed, and can always be
     exported for external backup.

4. Payment and License Keys
   Payment processing and license-key issuance/validation are performed
   through Lemon Squeezy (https://lemonsqueezy.com). Payment methods,
   tax handling, and refund procedures are governed by Lemon Squeezy's
   terms of service.

5. Restrictions
   The User shall NOT:
   (a) Reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, or attempt to extract
       the source code of the Software;
   (b) Redistribute, sell, rent, lease, or sublicense the Software in
       whole or in part;
   (c) Share, forge, or tamper with license keys in an unauthorized
       manner;
   (d) Use circumvention techniques to renew the trial or obtain access
       to paid features;
   (e) Use the Software for any purpose that violates applicable laws.

6. Ownership of User Content
   All content created or entered by the User through the Software —
   including manuscripts, character information, events, relationships,
   and collection items — belongs to the User. The Developer claims no
   rights over such User content.

7. Refunds
   Refunds for paid subscriptions may be requested within fourteen (14)
   days of the date of payment, as further described in the Refund Policy
   at `legal/refund.en.md`. No payment occurs during the trial period,
   so the trial itself is not subject to refund.

8. Updates and Support
   The Developer may provide updates to the Software but is under no
   obligation to do so. Updates are not forcibly applied; only
   recommendation notices will be displayed.

9. Warranty Disclaimer
   THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE", WITHOUT WARRANTIES
